info.title: Get GTFS timetables, stops, and route shapes

get.summary: GTFS timetables, stops, and route shapes for Buses
get.description:
Please note the consolidated “buses” schedule for realtime does not yet exist.  Whilst a zip file may be returned, it will be an set of invalid csv or text files or may return erroneous data.  To get buses schedule data, please use schedules from individual agency IDs.  You can review the agencies you need by referring to the Reference Tables https://opendata.transport.nsw.gov.au/reference-tables 

The HEAD operation can be used to tell you if the content has changed (as GET may not return an HTTP 304 when no content has changed.)

For example, you may compare the Last-Modified header retrieved during a HEAD operation with the Last-Modified header retrieved during a previous GET operation. If the headers are the same, the content has not changed since the previous GET operation. If the headers are different, the content has changed since the previous GET operation.

200.description: The request has been processed successfully.

401.description: The application calling the API has not been authenticated.

404.description: The requested resource could not be found.

get.summary: GTFS timetables, stops, and route shapes for Transit Systems
get.description:
Please see the General Transit Feed Specification (GTFS) documentation here: https://gtfs.org/

Please review the Real time Buses Technical Documentation - https://opendata.transport.nsw.gov.au/documentation

For agency details, please refer to the ‘Overlapping agencies in GTFS feeds’ table, ‘For Realtime GTFS static timetable parameter’ column on https://opendata.transport.nsw.gov.au/reference-tables
